# Custom Key Derivation Function (KDF) - Illustrative - More complex ones exist
def derive_key(password, salt):
    """Derives an encryption key from a password and salt using SHA-256."""
    salted_password = salt + password.encode('utf-8')
    key = hashlib.sha256(salted_password).digest()
    return base64.urlsafe_b64encode(key).decode('utf-8') #Returns a string.
# Staged Encryption - Illustrates a more sophisticated approach to avoid single points of failure
def encrypt_file(filepath, key):
    """Encrypts a single file using AES."""
